<br>
Now, there are some mobs (giants, for instance) who are immune to Crowd Control.  They cannot be mezzed, or stunned for that matter (learned this the hard way myself).  Which is why some silly chanters (such as, well, me) use charm as a means of crowd control on these guys.  Charm is very unpredictable, unlike mez, so it could break at any second, or last for the entire duration of the spell.  And while there is some debate, I have found Charisma to be a MAJOR factor in charming.  Charisma under 140 and you may as well write your death wish if you are gonna try to charm (at least from my experience) But it seems to me that 140 is like the barrier... much over that does not seem to help to a noticable degree (again from my limited experience)<br>
<br>
Well hope that helps... if not, too bad =P hehe<br>
